184.body:
Algorithm report (done!) wrote about string-search with suffix array compare it with other string-search algorithms implement example with Rust # fn main() { let s = "akasaka"; let t = "kas"; // make suffix array (naive approach) let mut tmp_suffixes = vec![("", 0); s.len()]; for i in 0..s.len() { tmp_suffixes[i] = (&s[i..], i); } tmp_suffixes.sort_by(|x, y| x.cmp(y)); let mut suffix_array = Vec::new(); for i in 0..s.len() { suffix_array.push(tmp_suffixes[i].1); } // binary search let mut lb = -1; let mut ub = s.len() as i32; while ub - lb > 1 { let mid = (lb + (ub - lb) / 2) as usize; let from = suffix_array[mid]; if t[..] <= s[from..] { ub = mid as i32; } else { lb = mid as i32; } } // check let from = suffix_array[ub as usize]; let end = std::cmp::min(s.len() - 1, from + t.len()); println!("{}", if s[from..end] == t[..] { "Yes" } else { "No" });
# } gave up to implement SA-IS (I wanna do this in the near future.. Give me more time & powerful processor in my head..) Computer Vision 2 short quiz about geometric transformation.
